@startuml iam-user-management
' Requirements: L1-SEC-001, L2-SEC-001
' Source: docs/specs/security/L1.md, docs/specs/security/L2.md
title IAM User Resource Operations (list, create, update)
autonumber

actor "Administrator" as ADM
participant "HTTP API" as API
participant "Auth Middleware" as MW
participant "IAM Handler" as IAM
database "IAM Store" as DB

note over ADM, DB
  L2-SEC-001: GIVEN an authenticated administrator
  WHEN IAM list/create/update methods are called
  THEN responses follow documented IAM resource structures.
end note

== List users ==
ADM -> API : GET /api/iam/users
activate API
API -> MW : Authenticate(request)
activate MW
MW --> API : principal (administrator)
deactivate MW
API -> IAM : ListUsersQuery
activate IAM
IAM -> DB : select user records
activate DB
DB --> IAM : user rows
deactivate DB
IAM --> API : ListUsersResponse (documented user resource structure)
deactivate IAM
API --> ADM : 200 OK { users: [ { name, displayName, email, roles } ] }
deactivate API

== Create user ==
ADM -> API : POST /api/iam/users { name, displayName, email, roles }
activate API
API -> MW : Authenticate(request)
activate MW
MW --> API : principal (administrator)
deactivate MW
API -> IAM : CreateUserCommand
activate IAM
IAM -> IAM : validate name uniqueness and role references
IAM -> DB : insert user record
activate DB
DB --> IAM : stored
deactivate DB
IAM --> API : UserResource
deactivate IAM
API --> ADM : 201 Created { user }
deactivate API

== Update user ==
ADM -> API : PATCH /api/iam/users/{name} { displayName, roles }
activate API
API -> MW : Authenticate(request)
activate MW
MW --> API : principal (administrator)
deactivate MW
API -> IAM : UpdateUserCommand
activate IAM
IAM -> DB : load user record
activate DB
DB --> IAM : user row
deactivate DB
IAM -> IAM : apply field mask, validate role references
IAM -> DB : persist updated record
activate DB
DB --> IAM : stored
deactivate DB
IAM --> API : UserResource (updated)
deactivate IAM
API --> ADM : 200 OK { user }
deactivate API
@enduml
